      December 14, 2018
     </h4>
    </div>
    <h5>
     <img alt="Graphene" class="img_L" height="90" src="/images/graphene_90.jpg" width="90"/>
     <a href="https://news.ucr.edu/articles/2018/12/14/new-property-revealed-graphene-could-lead-better-performing-solar-panels" target="_blank">
      New property revealed in graphene could lead to better performing solar panels
     </a>
    </h5>
    <p>
     <span>
      <span>
       <span>
        An international research team, co-led by associate professor of physics and astronomy Nathaniel Gabor at UCR, has discovered a new mechanism for ultra-efficient charge and energy flow in graphene.
       </span>
       <br/>
      </span>
     </span>
    </p>
    <p>
     <a href="https://news.ucr.edu/articles/2018/12/14/new-property-revealed-graphene-could-lead-better-performing-solar-panels" target="_blank">
