      Natural mosquito repellent startup wins seed funding
     </a>
    </h5>
    <p>
     <span>
      <span>
       <span>
        A startup founded by UC Riverside molecular, cell and systems biology professor
       </span>
       <a href="https://mcsb.ucr.edu/faculty/anand.ray.html" target="_blank">
        Anandasankar Ray
       </a>
       <span>
        based on his discovery of natural mosquito repellent compounds, won $50,000 in seed funding in a competition between entrepreneurs from the University of California system.
       </span>
      </span>
     </span>
    </p>
